This paper deals with planning under uncertainty, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and robotics (cs.RO). The concept of metareasoning is also relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses planning algorithms (cs.PL) and their limitations, making this category a likely fit as well.
